<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="206" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1914,2014]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="206" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1914,1940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar" authorityYear="2021" box="[280,421,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuda">
<emphasis box="[280,421,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Lyroda nuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the anterior margin of clypeus with two sets of three teeth laterally, two teeth medially and two sets of two intermediate teeth, median set of clypeal teeth narrow and cuspidate (
<figureCitation box="[1350,1436,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Figs 12</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[181,213,1986,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,189,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 58–64. Anterior clypeal margins: 58. Lyroda aurea sp. nov. holotype ♀; 59. Lyroda nuda sp. nov. holotype ♀; 60. Lyroda salai Giner Marí. ♀; 61. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♀; 62. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♂; 63. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♀; 64. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141505/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">59</figureCitation>
). Forewing with infumation crossing two submarginal cells and apex of second discoidal cell (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1372,1987,2014]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). The most outstanding character which separates this species from all other Indian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[1007,1086,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1086,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Lyroda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is its very sparse body setation, particularly on the lower frons and the clypeus, giving these areas a glabrous appearance (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1309,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Figs 11 &amp; 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,222,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[354,458,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[468,489,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[506,592,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[615,676,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Head</emphasis>
. Head broader than long; HW1.30–1.35 × HL; IODc 1.13–1.20 × IODv; POD 1.09–1.11 × OOD; inner eye orbits at vertex parallel; vertex and frons punctate, slightly alutaceous, PIS on average ≥ to PD; median furrow distinctly dividing frons into two portions (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1188,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); clypeus almost bare (without setae), punctate, alutaceous, PIS on average ≥ PD, anterior margin of clypeus usually with one set of two cuspidate teeth medially and two sets of three prominent teeth at lateral margins, with two sets of two intermediate teeth (
<figureCitation box="[220,305,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Figs 12</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[341,373,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,189,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 58–64. Anterior clypeal margins: 58. Lyroda aurea sp. nov. holotype ♀; 59. Lyroda nuda sp. nov. holotype ♀; 60. Lyroda salai Giner Marí. ♀; 61. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♀; 62. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♂; 63. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♀; 64. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141505/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">59</figureCitation>
); mandible deeply cut near base to give rise to two tooth like prominences, distinctly incised at base on outer margin; antennae thin, scape as long as F2, F1 slightly longer (1.05–1.54 ×) than F2, F1 3.05–3.15 × its apical width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[199,280,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotal collar lower than scutum, with three prominent protuberances; anterior third of scutum with two medial, parallel carinae diverging posteriorly, scutum with medial longitudinal depression; propleuron with oblique furrow; mesopleuron convex; scutum, scutellum and metanotum alutaceous with fine dense punctures, PIS on average ≤ PD; forewing with blackish infumation crossing two submarginal cells and apex of second discoidal cell (
<figureCitation box="[207,290,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); hind tibiae with 7–9 spines on posterior external margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[199,336,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Propodeum.</emphasis>
Dorsum with median carina extending close to posterior margin where short transverse carinae are present, surface rugoso-reticulate (
<figureCitation box="[538,619,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), without lateral carina; occasionally rugae join to form carina-like structure, side shiny with minute punctures, PIS on average greater than PD, distinctly alutaceous (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1314,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); posterior surface with narrow, wedge shaped deep median furrow, side of furrow with somewhat sinuate rugae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[199,275,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Gaster</emphasis>
. Basal platform of first tergum approximately triangular with constriction, having distinct edges; width of Gt1 1.25–1.30 × its length (
<figureCitation box="[488,571,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); gaster micropunctate with microscopic setae, alutaceous; pygidium triangular with lateral carinae as in figure 18.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[199,296,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Vestiture</emphasis>
. Setae silvery; clypeus and lower frons almost glabrous, clypeus with very sparse setae mixed with scattered golden coloured long bristles (
<figureCitation box="[604,758,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Figs 11 &amp; 12</figureCitation>
); sparse scattered setae on base of mandible, antenna, gena, frons, vertex, posterior sides of pronotal collar, posterior and posterolateral area of scutum, lateral sides of scutellum and metanotum, tibiae, femora, all sides of propodeum, and sternal areas of thorax; discontinuous silvery band of pile on Gt1–Gt3 (
<figureCitation box="[352,436,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[193,1391,195,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[184,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Lyroda nuda Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 10. Habitus, lateral view; 11. Head, frontal view; 12. Lower half of head, frontal view; 13. Head &amp; thorax; 14. Propodeum, dorsal view; 15. Thorax, lateral view; 16. Forewing; 17. Gaster, dorsal view; 18. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141491/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); alutaceous with microscopic setae; pygidium with dense, stiff brown setae mixed with longer erect brown bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[199,336,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Colouration</emphasis>
. Black; mandible, tegula, tibial spurs and tarsal claws more or less ferruginous; wings hyaline, slightly infumated at two submarginal cells and at apex of second discoidal cell, veins testaceous, stigma, subcostal and radial cell blackish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis box="[199,303,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Variation</emphasis>
. On anterior clypeal margin, two intermediate sets of two teeth are usually present. Sometimes, however, the intermediate set is represented by a single tooth on one side compared to two teeth on the other side.
</paragraph>
