</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of the species ‘ 
<emphasis box="[636,701,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">nuda’</emphasis>
is a Latin feminine adjective derived from ‘nudus’ which means nude. A bare appearance of the clypeus and lower frons and sparse setae on other body parts distinguish this species from the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[318,397,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[318,397,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Lyroda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1554,1580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Discussion</emphasis>
. According to the key to 
<collectingRegion box="[619,711,1555,1581]" country="Oman" name="Shamal ash Sharqiyah" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Oriental</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[719,798,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[719,798,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Lyroda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, T. &amp; Cai, W. &amp; Li, Q." box="[952,1111,1555,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="143 - 147" refId="ref11187" refString="Li, T., Cai, W. &amp; Li, Q. (2009) Key to the Oriental species of Lyroda Say, with description of a new species from China (Hymenoptera: Crabronidae). Entomologica Americana, 115, 143 - 147. https: // doi. org / 10.1664 / 07 - RA- 005.1" type="journal article" year="2009">
Li 
<emphasis box="[985,1043,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
, females of this new species resemble 
<taxonomicName authority="Giner Mari" authorityName="Giner Mari" box="[259,475,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salai">
<emphasis box="[259,343,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">L. salai</emphasis>
Giner Marí
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[483,626,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan, 2021" authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan" authorityYear="2021" box="[532,626,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea" status="sp. nov.">L. aurea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[633,723,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[633,723,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having a similar arrangement of teeth on the anterior clypeal margin and shape of medial sets of teeth and infumation pattern on forewing. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar" authorityYear="2021" box="[1031,1174,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuda">
<emphasis box="[1031,1174,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Lyroda nuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, is characterized by very sparse silvery setae, especially on the clypeus and lower frons and sparse on the antenna, gena, frons, vertex, posterior side of pronotal collar, posterior and posterolateral area of scutum, lateral sides of scutellum and metanotum, tibiae, femora, all sides of propodeum and sternal areas of thorax, giving a glabrous appearance to these areas (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan, 2021" authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan" authorityYear="2021" box="[257,352,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[257,352,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">L. aurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[361,452,1771,1797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[361,452,1771,1797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
dense golden setae are present on the clypeus, lower frons, and other mentioned body parts; in 
<taxonomicName authority="Giner Mari" authorityName="Giner Mari" box="[252,471,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salai">
<emphasis box="[252,336,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">L. salai</emphasis>
Giner Marí
</taxonomicName>
, dense silvery setae are present on antennae, frons, clypeus, gena, tibiae, femora and both lateral and sternal areas of the thorax). In 
<taxonomicName authority="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan, 2021" authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan" authorityYear="2021" box="[668,753,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuda" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[668,753,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">L. nuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[759,848,1843,1869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[759,848,1843,1869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
punctures on the clypeus and lower frons are sparser than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan, 2021" authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan" authorityYear="2021" box="[234,327,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[234,327,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">L. aurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[333,422,1879,1905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[333,422,1879,1905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, PIS being on average ≥ PD (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan, 2021" authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan" authorityYear="2021" box="[779,872,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[779,872,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">L. aurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[878,967,1879,1905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[878,967,1879,1905]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, punctures on the clypeus and lower frons are denser, PIS on average ≤ PD).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
